    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 space-y-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase text-center text-white tracking-tight">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div class="space-y-2">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">Is DownKingo free?</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Yes, DownKingo is 100% free and open source. There are no hidden fees, subscriptions, or ads inside the app.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="space-y-2">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">What platforms are supported?</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">We officially support the 12 major platforms listed above, but the underlying engine (yt-dlp) supports over 1000 websites.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-2">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">Do I need to install anything?</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Yes, DownKingo is a powerful desktop application for Windows, Linux, and macOS. It is not a browser extension.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-2">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">Is it safe?</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Absolutely. The code is open source on GitHub for anyone to audit. We respect your privacy and do not track your download history.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
